Steganography is the technique of hiding secret data within an ordinary, non-secret, file or message in order to avoid detection;

The use of steganography can be combined with encryption as an extra step for hiding or protecting data.

Steganography is the practice of hiding information inside something that appears normal and is not secret.

Cybercriminals use steganography to hide stolen data or malicious code in images, audio files and other media

The word steganography comes from Greek steganographia, which combines or concealed and -graphia meaning writing
